    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-24T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-24T20:00:00-05:00" n="139"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d139">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.20/8–2544: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-25T08:00:00+07:00"
                            >August 25, 1944—8 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 28—1:58 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1455. Naval Attaché states he now has reports from three separate Chinese sources
                    regarding holding of military conferences designed to reform Chinese Army (re
                    telegram 1432, August 19th) which are expected to terminate in about a week.
                    Press announcement today of appointment new director [of] Conscription
                    Administration [of] War Ministry<note n="59" xml:id="d139fn59">Lt. Gen. Hsu
                        Sze-ping.</note> presumably result of conferences.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
